The paper is about a robot simulator for swarm and collective robotics, which falls under the robotics (RO) sub-category. The use of evolutionary swarm robotics and distributed evolutionary optimization suggests a focus on machine learning (MA) and artificial intelligence (AI). The mention of self-adaptation and embodied morphogenesis suggests a focus on systems and control (SY). Finally, the use of online onboard embodied evolution suggests a focus on machine learning and reinforcement learning (LG).
